<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="338" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1936,2033]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="337" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1936,1961]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[355,546,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">General features</emphasis>
—Idiosoma elongated-oval; gnathosomal bay U-shaped, proximally rounded; Cxgl-4 subapical, only slightly posterior to Cx-I tips; suture line of Cx-IV distinct, extending posteriorly beyond posterior margin of genital field; excretory pore in a medioposterior indentation of primary sclerotization, Vgl-2 posterior to excretory pore; gnathosomal rostrum long, ventral margin strongly curved (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1281,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); P-2 ventral margin slightly curved, ventrodistal protrusion slender, spatula-shaped, distally finely serrate; ventrodistal projection at P-3 irregularly cone-shaped, anterior margin frayed; P-4 relatively short, dorsal margin weakly curved, with ventral tubercles pointed and separated, bearing one long and three short setae (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1350,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Figs. 3F–G</figureCitation>
). Male: medial suture line of Cx-II+III short; genital field subrectangular in shape; posterior suture lines of Cx-IV starting at right angle from genital field (
<figureCitation box="[536,627,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory complex apically long, cella proximalis small (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1423,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Female: genital field roundish in shape
</paragraph>
