<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1015,1040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[322,521,1015,1040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" refId="ref7723" refString="Smit, H., Pesic, V. &amp; Mary-Sasal, N. (2010) Second contribution to the knowledge of water mites from the Comoros, with the description of one new species (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Zootaxa, 2413, 51 - 60." type="journal article">
Smit 
<emphasis box="[382,432,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
reported a single female of 
<emphasis box="[836,972,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Torrenticola</emphasis>
from Dembéni River. Later on, the same authors assigned this specimen to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Smit, 2015" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[538,947,1052,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[538,715,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
Pešić &amp; Smit, 2015
</taxonomicName>
described originally on the basis of a male and female from a tributary of Koualé River (Pešić 
<emphasis box="[728,778,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2015a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">
Additional material of this study reveals that females from Dembéni River fit perfectly the description of the unnamed specimen described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[524,725,1159,1184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" refId="ref7723" refString="Smit, H., Pesic, V. &amp; Mary-Sasal, N. (2010) Second contribution to the knowledge of water mites from the Comoros, with the description of one new species (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Zootaxa, 2413, 51 - 60." type="journal article">
Smit 
<emphasis box="[584,634,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
, but they have to be assigned to the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Mary, 2018" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Mary" authorityYear="2018" box="[1276,1436,1161,1184]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayottensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1276,1436,1161,1184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. mayottensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,245,1196,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,245,1196,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[621,802,1197,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[621,802,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(data taken from Pešić 
<emphasis box="[1094,1149,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2015a) in a number of morphological features: 1) dorsal shield with a colour pattern (without colour in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[1078,1257,1233,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[1078,1257,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, compare 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[315,1273,1122,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[315,1279,1122,1910]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 11. Photographs of dorsal (A, C–E) and ventral (B, F): A–B Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male holotype. C–D Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov.: C = male holotype, F = female paratype. E–F Djeboa davecooki sp. nov., male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437808/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Figs. 11C–D</figureCitation>
with 
<figureCitation box="[299,434,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[212,1372,449,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[210,1378,445,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., female, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = palp, medial view. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437792/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Figs. 4A, D</figureCitation>
in Pešić 
<emphasis box="[543,595,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2015a), 2) gnathosomal rostrum comparatively longer (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1351,1436,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
with 
<figureCitation box="[208,295,1303,1328]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,196,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male, Koualé River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = IV-L-5 and -6; D = I-L; E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
in Pešić 
<emphasis box="[397,447,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2015a), and 3) P-4 stouter in the both sexes, L/H 2.4–3.0 (
<quantity box="[1118,1233,1303,1328]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.271" metricValueMax="9.398" metricValueMin="9.144" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" unit="in" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.7 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[1240,1417,1305,1328]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[1240,1417,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The female of the new species can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[744,920,1341,1364]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[744,920,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of more roundish genital field, L/ W 0.95–1.05 
<emphasis box="[305,328,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">vs</emphasis>
. more elongated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2015" box="[555,733,1377,1400]" class="Arachnida" family="Athienemanniidae" genus="Africasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorosensis">
<emphasis box="[555,733,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">T. comorosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, L/W ratio 1.12 (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1039,1124,1375,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[212,1372,449,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[210,1378,445,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., female, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = palp, medial view. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437792/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
with 
<figureCitation box="[1190,1274,1375,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,366,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,360,1796]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Torrenticola mayottensis sp. nov., male, Dembéni River, Mayotte: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = ventral; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F = palp, lateral view; G = palp, medial view (P-1 lacking). Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437790/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
in Pešić 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">et al</emphasis>
. 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
